sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K125830
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device codes for signal sequence-GFP fusion protein designed for nitrate-inducible secretion of GFP by Synechocystis sp. PCC6803.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Krystle Salazar and Grace Kwan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The rbs is current BioBrick part BBa_B0034, respectively. The signal sequence slr2016 and nir promoter is derived from the genome of Synechocystis sp. PCC6803. The GFP fusion is derived from the BioBrick part for GFP, BBa_E0040.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K125100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Krystle Salazar and Grace Kwan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The ''nirA'' promoter originates from ''Synechocystis'' sp. PCC6803.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: slr2016 SS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: slr2016 signal sequence from cyanobacterium Synechocystis; secretes protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Krystle Salazar and Grace Kwan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The ''slr2016'' signal sequence is located at the amino terminus of slr2016 polypeptides synthesized by ''Synechocystis'' sp. PCC 6803.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K125500
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Grace Kwan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The GFP fusion brick was derived from the GFP BioBrick, [http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_E0040 BBa_E0040].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The first two nucleotides of the GFP start codon were removed to create this fusion brick.
